@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

    The FreeDL door checks the list of tagged files that the user
    currently has, and if it finds that one of them is a free download
    then it will adjust the Flags by setting TF_FREEDOWNLOAD.

    It will match filenames by loading a plain text file called
    "FreeDLList.TXT" from the conference's path, e.g:

    "HBBS:Conferences/FileConf1/FreeDLList.TXT"

    If it can't find a match there it will load the file

    "HBBS:System/Data/FreeDLList.TXT"

    And will try to find a match again.

    If the filename is matched (case insensitive) the file will be
    marked as a free download and all doors that are aware of the
    TF_FREEDOWNLOAD flag will act accordingly.

    Door coders should read this file fully.

@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    The doors is stored as HBBS:Doors/System/FreeDL/FreeDL.HBBS

    This is included and enabled with a fresh installation of HydraBBS
    since V1.04.  Users of prior version should do this:

    Add the following lines to the appropriate "commands/system" file:

    FreeDL_Type_1=HBBS
    FreeDL_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/Adverts/Adverts.HBBS {N} {O}

    See HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/Commands/System for an example

@EndNode

