@EndNode

@Node CmdLineOptions "CmdLineOptions"

  Command Line Options
  ====================

    LASTONLY - if specifed only the last tagged files will be checked

    # - if a number is specified, the LAST # tagged files will be checked.

    <filename> - if a filename (no path) is specified, then the list of
                 tagged files will be checked, and if the user has this
                 file tagged then it will be flagged as a free download.

    If no arguments are specified then all of them will be checked.


    An example of using the <filename> option would be (say) from a
    screen file, you could do @^SYSDOOR^FREEDL FileList.TXT@ to make
    the filelist.txt a free download.

    Likewise, a door coder that has just coded a filelist downloader
    door could make his door pack the file lists into an lha
    archive, tag this file using the system door "Tag_File" and then
    in the door program he could call:

    DOOR_SystemDoor("FREEDL","FileList.TXT");

    Isn't this just great... :=)

@EndNode

