@Node ToDo "ToDo"

  ToDo
  ====

    Optimise, so that the FreeDLlist.TXT's are not loaded several times
    when checking more than one tag at a time. (Arghh..)

    Option for free download dates and times (i.e. if the user calls between
    two times or between two times on a specified date or on a specified date
    then make *all* the downloads free! add another flag called
    TF_FREEDOWNLOADTHISCALL so that the TF_FREEDOWNLOAD flag could be removed
    at loggoff.

    This requires working around the fact that a user could call, flag files
    and log off with them still flagged.  so the best way of getting round
    this would be to call the FreeDL door, when the user logs off, with
    another option so that it can remove the TF_FREEDOWNLOAD flag if the
    TF_FREEDOWNLOADTHISCALL is set.

    Then at login time, all flagged files with TF_FREEDOWNLOADTHISCALL
    have to be rechecked, simply by calling this door with no paramaters.

@EndNode

